---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Ornament from '~/components/ui/Ornament.astro';
import Badge from '~/components/ui/Badge.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="M.V. Porkchop Express"
  description="The M.V. Porkchop Express, a 2023 Sun Tracker Party Barge 22 DLX of the Miccosukee Yacht Club. Lake Talquin and the St. Marks River."
  active="about"
>

  <section class="vessel-header">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/#fleet" class="back-link">&larr; The Fleet</a>
      <div class="vessel-badges">
        <Badge tone="brass">Pontoon &middot; Sun Tracker 22 DLX</Badge>
        <Badge tone="paper">2023</Badge>
        <Badge tone="paper">Lake Talquin &middot; St. Marks River</Badge>
      </div>
      <h1>M.V. Porkchop Express</h1>
      <p class="lead vessel-lead">
        The Club's pontoon. A 2023 Sun Tracker Party Barge 22 DLX with a Mercury 150
        four-stroke outboard. Operated by Captain Harris on Lake Talquin and the St. Marks River.
        Comfortably accommodates the entire club and several coolers besides.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="vessel-photo-full">
    <img src="/assets/porkchop-express.jpg" alt="M.V. Porkchop Express on the trailer" />
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="narrow">

      <h2>The Vessel</h2>
      <p>
        The Sun Tracker Party Barge 22 DLX is a recreational pontoon built on an all-welded
        aluminum platform with 24-inch diameter marine alloy pontoon logs, a full-width swim
        deck, and enough seating for eleven persons before anyone starts making decisions
        about personal space. Sun Tracker has been producing pontoon boats since 1978 and
        backs the hull with a limited lifetime warranty, which is the sort of confidence that
        comes from building the same basic thing for several decades and learning from it.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Club's example was acquired in 2023 and fitted with the Mercury 150 four-stroke
        outboard &mdash; the top option in the lineup, and the correct choice for a vessel
        whose operating waters include the St. Marks River, where conditions can require
        prompt acceleration. In that configuration, the boat is estimated at 29 to 38 miles
        per hour, though the Club has not found it necessary to establish the upper end of
        that range.
      </p>

      <Ornament />

      <h2>On the Water</h2>
      <p>
        The Porkchop Express operates primarily on Lake Talquin and the St. Marks River,
        both in Leon and Wakulla counties. Lake Talquin, formed by the impoundment of the
        Ochlockonee River, offers 8,800 acres of fishable, cruisable water at depths
        sufficient for pontoon operation and the occasional ambitious cooler deployment.
        The St. Marks River runs south through Wakulla County to the Gulf, with a character
        somewhat more serious than Lake Talquin and cypress trees that justify the transit.
      </p>
      <p>
        The 22 DLX is not a performance vessel in any category that performance sailors
        would recognize. It is, however, an exceptionally capable leisure platform. The
        powered 10-foot Bimini deploys at the push of a button. The patented STOW MORE
        seat system provides underseat and seat-back storage sufficient to organize a
        properly provisioned Club outing. The Bluetooth stereo system has not yet been
        the subject of any formal Club complaints, though the season is young.
      </p>

      <Ornament />

      <h2>On the Name</h2>
      <p>
        The vessel is named for the <em>Porkchop Express</em>, the fictional 18-wheel truck
        driven by Jack Burton in the 1986 John Carpenter film <em>Big Trouble in Little China</em>.
        Captain Harris has not provided a formal explanation for this choice, which the Club
        considers explanation enough.
      </p>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-paper">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="specs-header">
        <span class="eyebrow-rule">Technical Register</span>
        <h2>Specifications</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="specs-grid">
        <div class="specs-group">
          <div class="specs-group-label">Dimensions</div>
          <dl>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>LOA</dt><dd>24' 2"</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Deck Length</dt><dd>22' 1"</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Beam</dt><dd>8' 6"</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Log Diameter</dt><dd>24"</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Log Length</dt><dd>22' 3"</dd></div>
          </dl>
        </div>
        <div class="specs-group">
          <div class="specs-group-label">Weight & Capacity</div>
          <dl>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Dry Weight</dt><dd>2,080 lbs</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Max Persons</dt><dd>11</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Max Weight</dt><dd>2,200 lbs</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Fuel Capacity</dt><dd>32.1 gal</dd></div>
          </dl>
        </div>
        <div class="specs-group">
          <div class="specs-group-label">Mechanical</div>
          <dl>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Engine</dt><dd>Mercury 150 L</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Type</dt><dd>Four-stroke outboard</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Power</dt><dd>150 hp</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Est. Speed</dt><dd>29 &ndash; 38 mph</dd></div>
          </dl>
        </div>
        <div class="specs-group">
          <div class="specs-group-label">The Club's Vessel</div>
          <dl>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Year</dt><dd>2023</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Captain</dt><dd>J. B. Harris</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Home Waters</dt><dd>Lake Talquin</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Also Runs</dt><dd>St. Marks River</dd></div>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
.vessel-header {
  background: var(--bg-deep);
  color: var(--fg-on-deep);
  padding-block: var(--space-9) var(--space-8);
}
.back-link {
  display: inline-block;
  font-family: var(--font-sans);
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wide);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--brass-200);
  text-decoration: none;
  margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  transition: color var(--dur-fast) var(--ease-out);
}
.back-link:hover { color: var(--sail-50); }
.vessel-badges { display: flex; gap: var(--space-2); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); flex-wrap: wrap; }
.vessel-header h1 {
  color: var(--sail-50);
  font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, var(--fs-display));
  margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
}
.vessel-lead {
  color: var(--fg-on-deep-muted);
  max-width: 58ch;
}

.vessel-photo-full {
  background: var(--navy-900);
  height: 480px;
  overflow: hidden;
}
.vessel-photo-full img {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
  object-position: center 40%;
  opacity: 0.9;
}

.specs-header {
  text-align: center;
  margin-bottom: var(--space-7);
}
.specs-header h2 { margin-top: var(--space-4); }
.specs-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
  gap: var(--space-6);
}
.specs-group-label {
  font-family: var(--font-sans);
  font-size: var(--fs-overline);
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: var(--tracking-xwide);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--brass-600);
  margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  padding-bottom: var(--space-3);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}
dl { margin: 0; }
.spec-row {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  gap: var(--space-4);
  padding-block: 6px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  font-size: 14px;
}
.spec-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
dt {
  font-family: var(--font-sans);
  font-weight: 500;
  color: var(--fg-muted);
}
dd {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 13px;
  color: var(--fg);
  margin: 0;
  text-align: right;
}

@media (max-width: 900px) {
  .specs-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
  .vessel-photo-full { height: 300px; }
}
@media (max-width: 600px) {
  .specs-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
}
</style>
